			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Got 2 linux machines running Gentoo 2.6 kernel.
<br />

<br />
I'm running an Apache web server on one but I have a couple questions about security.
<br />

<br />
1.)  How much native security is in Apache2 right out of the box?  I'm assuming none.
<br />

<br />
2.)  If the ansewr to 1 is "very little", then what should be done?  Also, are there security patches in the OS that will help?
<br />

<br />
3.)  I looked at my access logs and saw some weird POST/GET requests.  Not sure what that is but i disabled the web server until I can block access to that.  Is that an obvious gaping hole I have left open?  If so, what can be done to restrict users to the directory of my files and ONLY that directory.
<br />

<br />
I just want to know what I should do to step up security but still allow dynamic pages and scripting.
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance!<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
