			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				You will get a lot of post/gets from hacked IIS machines that are trying to do buffer overruns, bots looking for vulnerable PHP sites, etc.  At work, network security asked us to upgrade our boxen to apache 2.0.52 due to some vulnerability.  I couldn't find an RPM for RH9 and ended up compiling.  Some people like to run apache in <a href="http://www.faqs.org/docs/securing/chap29sec254.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">chroot jail</a>, but I haven't yet and don't plan to until one of my boxes is hacked.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
