			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Apache out of the box is fairly stable and safe.
<br />

<br />
Watch <a href="http://www.apache.org" target="_blank">www.apache.org</a> for security announcements but for the most part the software is very mature and most vulnerabilities have been discovered and closed.
<br />

<br />
Whenever you install or "load" a new module check the security issues for it as well.  If you do something foolish like allow fiel upload you will have a major breach.  Some versions of mod_php and the executables that it invokes are vulnerable as was mentioned before.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
