			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Offtopic
<br />

<br />
I'm looking to implement a network management system.  To date I've been using mon/mon.cgi and sawdog for monitoring/alarming; mrtg for bandwidth utilization and smokeping to visualize network health.  
<br />

<br />
Some of the oss projects that have caught my eye are :
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.crystalballinc.com/vlad/software/ossmon/" target="_blank">http://www.crystalballinc.com/vlad/software/ossmon/</a> 
<br />
<a href="http://wiki.opennms.org/tiki-index.php" target="_blank">http://wiki.opennms.org/tiki-index.php</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.zabbix.com/" target="_blank">http://www.zabbix.com/</a>
<br />
<a href="http://moodss.sourceforge.net/" target="_blank">http://moodss.sourceforge.net/</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.evalesco.com/" target="_blank">http://www.evalesco.com/</a>
<br />

<br />
Any of you use/have used these?  Any that I don't have listed that I should check out? I want to monitor a variety of systems: *nix,windows:fileservers/exchange/AD,cisco routers,other snmp devices.  I know I can get the functionality with just mon or sawdog but I need somehting a little more pretty for management.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
