				<div class="postbody">
				We're tackling that same thing at work, lokal. My personal opinion is that all network management software I have ever seen is, quite plainly, garbage. We're trying to make What's Up Gold from ipswitch do the job for now (management likes the interface, I still think it's a turd under the hood). It is very hard to find good network management software that works well across all platforms. I've been through all the free ones such as nagios/netsaint, big brother/sister, zabblix etc and half a dozen commercial ones. Nothing meets all my needs, and most of them require the used to be highly technically advanced. I've found nothing that makes for a manager-friendly solution. All of them require hacking to make the cross-platform views work.
<br />

<br />
You listed a couple that I haven't seen before; I'll check them out when I get a chance.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
