			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				So far it looks like I'll be hobbling together a variety of packages.  I think I will be switching away from mon &amp; sawdog to nagios (netsaint has come a long ways in the past few years.) for the actual monitoring/alerting.
<br />

<br />
I've been using <a href="http://people.ee.ethz.ch/~oetiker/webtools/smokeping/" target="_blank" class="postlink">smokeping</a> to keep an eye on our satellite network and I really like it so it gets to stay.
<br />

<br />
I've also setup <a href="http://www.cacti.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">cacti</a> and I'm pretty pleased visually with the output.  I like the way it allows you to choose the time periods you wish to view and it is pretty extensible.
<br />

<br />
I checked out the moodss package briefly, I think it has potential for our monitoring stations.  I tried to get the aolserver/ossmon up and running but it wasn't a smooth install so I moved on; I may try again as it did look interesting.  I haven't setup the opennms product yet; if I do and it is as useful as nagios I may lean towards it instead.
<br />

<br />
Those screenshots look pretty good Lanol; if I didn't have the time to do all this research lately I'd probably give it a serious look; and I still may!<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
