				<div class="postbody">
				I'm in the same NMS boat right now, and looking to simplify. So far I've got mrtg/rrdtool loosely monitoring network devices, but it's a bitch to setup and maintain. Also an open source product called Argus probing servers/services. Awstats parsing web/mail logs, yadda yadda. On top of all that is a mountain of half assed perl/php scripts putting it altogether.
<br />

<br />
Whats Up Professional looked good on paper, but their demo was mighty disappointing. That EM7 product looks pretty cool, I'll check that out. Nagios too.
<br />

<br />
In the end the management wants pretty graphs, and the rest of everyone wants a "easy to use interface, like the windows xp".  <img src="images/smiles/frown.gif" alt="frown" border="0" /> All I want is an easier way to graph server specific stats.. partition usage, RAM, temperature, etc. Maybe babysit MSSQL to make sure it's a happy camper.<br />
